commit.message:
display: always use "%s"-style format for printf()-style functions

    `ncuses-6.3` added printf-style function attributes and now makes
    it easier to catch cases when user input is used in palce of format
    string when built with CFLAGS=-Werror=format-security:

    display-main.c:59:9: error: format not a string literal and no format arguments [-Werror=format-security]
       59 |         wprintw(dump_win, str);
          |         ^~~~~~~

Let's wrap all the missing places with "%s" format.

libuwifi: update submodule

Otherwise build fails as:

      CC      conf_options.c
    In file included from conf_options.c:29:
    main.h:27:10: fatal error: uwifi/cc_list.h: No such file or directory
       27 | #include <uwifi/cc_list.h>
          |          ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Closes: https://github.com/br101/horst/issues/108
Adapt to function rename of cc_list
Improve main window layout, fix parsing (uwifi)
Return on zero rate (should not happen)

Rename wlan_src to wlan_ta and wlan_dst to wlan_ra

Like in libuwifi and WLAN standard
Fix setting of VHT80 channels from UI
PROBE is not a WLAN mode like AP or STA
